tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE BuildingMaterials (
    material_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    material_name TEXT,
    material_type TEXT,
    price DECIMAL,
    quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE building_materials (material_id INT PRIMARY KEY, material_name STRING, material_density FLOAT);

CREATE TABLE structural_analysis (analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY, analysis_name STRING, material_id INT REFERENCES building_materials(material_id), load_condition STRING);

CREATE TABLE material_properties (
  property_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_id INT NOT NULL,
  property_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  property_value VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES building_materials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE structural_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_id INT NOT NULL,
  analysis_date DATE NOT NULL,
  analysis_result VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES building_materials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE MaterialProperties (
  prop_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_id INT,
  property_name VARCHAR(100),
  property_value DECIMAL(10, 2),
  FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES BuildingMaterials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE StructuralElements (
  element_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  element_type VARCHAR(50),
  material_id INT,
  element_length DECIMAL(10, 2),
  FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES BuildingMaterials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE AnalysisResults (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  element_id INT,
  analysis_type VARCHAR(50),
  result_value DECIMAL(10, 2),
  FOREIGN KEY (element_id) REFERENCES StructuralElements(element_id)
);

CREATE TABLE BuildingMaterials (
    material_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    material_name VARCHAR(255),
    material_type VARCHAR(100),
    material_density FLOAT,
    material_strength FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE MaterialProperties (
    property_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    material_id INT,
    property_name VARCHAR(255),
    property_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES BuildingMaterials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE StructuralAnalysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    material_id INT,
    load_type VARCHAR(100),
    analysis_result VARCHAR(255),
    FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES BuildingMaterials(material_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ProjectMaterials (
    project_id INT,
    material_id INT,
    quantity INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (project_id, material_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (project_id) REFERENCES ProjectDetails(project_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (material_id) REFERENCES BuildingMaterials(material_id)
);
